Johannesburg - A toddler drowned in a swimming pool in Amanzimtoti, Durban, on Thursday, paramedics said.Netcare 911 spokesperson Jeffrey Wicks said the 2-year-old boy was pulled out of the pool by a relative who initiated CPR until paramedics arrived.Paramedics tried to resuscitate the child, but he was declared dead at the scene.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.